Clearstream, Highland Gold, Compass: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-09-20T06:41:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/clearstream-highland-gold-rbs-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and
Irish markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last market close.  The FTSE 100 Index fell 108.85 points, or 2 percent, to
5,259.56 yesterday . The FTSE All-Share Index dropped 2 percent
and Ireland’s ISEQ Index declined 1.6 percent.  Clearstream Technologies Group Plc (CTN)  : C.R. Bard Inc.
agreed to buy Clearstream, an Irish maker of medical devices,
for about 43.8 million pounds ($69 million) in cash. The shares
were unchanged at 46.13 pence.  Highland Gold Mining Ltd. (HGM)  : The Russian gold
producer said first-half sales rose to $158.1 million from
$100.5 million and net income after tax increased to $70.3
million from $23.3 million. The stock was unchanged at 192.5
pence.  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS)  : RBS said Tom
Majewski has joined the firm’s global banking & markets division
in the Americas as a managing director in its asset-backed
finance coverage and advisory team. The stock tumbled 5.7
percent to 22.88 pence.  Compass Group Plc (CPG)  : RBC Capital Markets downgraded
the stock to “sector perform” from “top pick.” The shares
slipped 1.1 percent to 553 pence.  Rio Tinto Plc (RIO)  : The world’s second-biggest mining
company said it has increased its copper mineral resources by 20
million tons to 106 million tons at its wholly-owned Utah Copper
Bingham Canyon Mine. The company also said its order books are
full and commodity prices remain robust. The shares fell 3.3
percent to 3,505 pence.  Debenhams Plc (DEB)  : U.K.’s second-largest department-
store owner said its gross margin may show no change or fall
“slightly” this year, though pretax profit will probably
exceed consensus estimates. The shares declined 0.5 percent to
59.3 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
